<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="439" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1387,1882]" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1387,1414]" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae greenish yellow without stains. Antennomer II longer than III. Pronotum with a light brown posterior band; posterolateral angles somewhat developed, more than eye width, and curved backwards (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1424,1424,1450]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[323,1261,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[284,1304,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 17. H. balteatus. A—dorsal view; B—ventral; C—Female; D—specimen data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677903/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
). Anterior part of scutellum with punctures located in dark spots barely larger than punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1306,1460,1486]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[323,1261,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[284,1304,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 17. H. balteatus. A—dorsal view; B—ventral; C—Female; D—specimen data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677903/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
). Meso and metapleuron with a pair of faded brown rounded spots on base of each coxae (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1122,1496,1522]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[323,1261,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[284,1304,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 17. H. balteatus. A—dorsal view; B—ventral; C—Female; D—specimen data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677903/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Fig. 17B</figureCitation>
). The excavation of anterior lobes of metasternal process shallow, harboring fourth rostral segment and distal part of third (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1338,1532,1558]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[323,1261,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[284,1304,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 17. H. balteatus. A—dorsal view; B—ventral; C—Female; D—specimen data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677903/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Fig. 17B</figureCitation>
). Brown spots on apex of abdominal sutures faded (
<figureCitation box="[637,740,1568,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[323,1261,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[284,1304,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 17. H. balteatus. A—dorsal view; B—ventral; C—Female; D—specimen data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677903/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Fig. 17B</figureCitation>
). Female (
<figureCitation box="[860,964,1568,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[323,1261,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[284,1304,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 17. H. balteatus. A—dorsal view; B—ventral; C—Female; D—specimen data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677903/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Fig. 17C</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites 8 posterior margin sinuous with outer angle slightly projected and rounded; imaginary line tangent to angles reaching middle of gonocoxites 9; gonocoxites 8 covering only base of gonocoxites 9; sutural border with a shallow distal excavation. Gonapophyses 8 barely visible. Laterotergites 9 with base shallowly excavated; apex slightly surpassing band uniting laterotergites 8. Male unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="439" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,1387,1882]" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1747,1774]" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was described from a quick examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1025,1073,1748,1774]" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">type</typeStatus>
in the collection of The Natural History Museum in April, 2019 and photos taken with compact digital camera (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1142,1784,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[323,1261,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[284,1304,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 17. H. balteatus. A—dorsal view; B—ventral; C—Female; D—specimen data." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677903/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="439">Fig. 17D</figureCitation>
). A comparative diagnosis will be made with new species that will be described in an upcoming paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
